com.vechain.thorclient.clients

Class ProtoTypeContractClient

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.vechain.thorclient.clients.base.AbstractClient
      • com.vechain.thorclient.clients.TransactionClient
        • com.vechain.thorclient.clients.ProtoTypeContractClient

  • public class ProtoTypeContractClient
extends TransactionClient
    ProtoType Contract is a native contract for user to do multiple parties payment(mpp). Prototype
    What is ProtoType for?
    In common scenario, if a sender A want to make a transaction to target B, the sender A need to pay the transaction fee(gas). However, for some realistic reason, the target A want to pay the transaction fee. Then the mpp can do such a thing. The sender A can be a user of target B(addUsers(Address[], Address[], int, byte, int, ECKeyPair)), then the target B can set user plan (credit and recovery) for all senders. After all the things is done, then the sender A do transaction to target B, if the fee is less than the credit, the ProtoType native contract is going to book fee(gas) from target B's account.
    How to use ProtoType?
    First, you must be the master of the to address. By call setMasterAddress(com.vechain.thorclient.core.model.clients.Address[], com.vechain.thorclient.core.model.clients.Address[], int, byte, int, com.vechain.thorclient.utils.crypto.ECKeyPair), then you can query the master by getMasterAddress(Address, Revision) Second, you as a Master, you can set add user to user plan. This step is to set candidate, the one you want to give credit. addUsers(Address[], Address[], int, byte, int, ECKeyPair) Third, set a user plan to target address for all users on the users list. setCreditPlans(Address[], Amount[], Amount[], int, byte, int, ECKeyPair)
